# bad_hosts_central
# =================
# Same syntax and matching semantics as bad_hosts, but intended for a shared or
# centrally maintained list. Local exceptions belong in bad_hosts.
#
# Every active line should have documented evidence, a maintainer, an inclusion
# criterion, and a removal criterion in the central-list repository.
#
# Exact host:
# ^reader99\.abusive-provider\.example$
#
# Bounded numbered farm:
# ^reader(?:[1-9]|1[0-9]|20)\.abusive-provider\.example$
#
# Two exact IPv4 addresses:
# ^(?:192\.0\.2\.44|192\.0\.2\.45)$
#
# One IPv6 documentation prefix:
# ^2001:db8:bad:
#
# Keep this file atomically replaceable. The mtime reload mechanism retains the
# last successfully compiled expression when an update is invalid.
